10/21/83  send_mail request:  preface, prf

Syntax:  prf path


Function:  writes the printed representation of the message to the
beginning of an existing segment.


Arguments:
path
   is the pathname of the segment to which the message is written.  The
   suffix "mail" is added if necessary.


Notes:
If the segment identified by the path argument does not exist, the user
is queried for permission to create it.  If the segment does exist, its
previous contents are moved "down" to make room for the message written
by this request.
